  "description": "<section id=\"description\">\n<p><code>I'd be happy to</code> followed by a verb is a polite and positive way to agree to do something. <code>I'd</code> is a contraction of <code>I would</code>, which is used to talk about a willingness or offer to do something in the future.</p>\n<p>For example, if someone asks if you can help them study English, you can say, <code>I'd be happy to help</code>, meaning you are willing and pleased to help them.</p>\n</section>",
